Shortfalls in the vault may occur prior to the period reviewed in the vault access log. Occasionally, vault access may not be recorded on the log.

 

When reviewing this document, look for items such as:

 

  • Failure to require dual controls for vault access (e.g., head teller entering the vault alone)
  • Indications that the vault was accessed periodically throughout the day (e.g., not needing to access the vault throughout the day is very unusual)
